      "content": "Over-the-counter ear drops may help soften wax, but they aren't a guaranteed solution, especially if it's an impaction. Self-treatment in an ear with such symptoms can be risky and might lead to further complications. If you're pressed for time, you could try to gently flush your ear with warm water to help dislodge the wax, but be careful not to push anything deeper. However, if the blockage persists or if you're unsure, it's important to prioritize your health over convenience. A healthcare professional can provide a safe and effective treatment plan tailored to your situation. Even a quick consultation could prevent potential problems. Your hearing and ear health are worth that brief visit.",
      "source": "target",
